#!perl

our $DATE = '2019-09-29'; # DATE
our $VERSION = '0.002'; # VERSION

use strict;
use warnings;

use File::MoreUtil 'dir_has_dot_subdirs';

unless (@ARGV == 1) {
    die "Usage: dir-has-dot-subdirs <path>\n";
}

exit(dir_has_dot_subdirs($ARGV[0]) ? 0:1);

# ABSTRACT: Test that a directory has dot subdirectories
# PODNAME: dir-has-dot-subdirs

__END__

=pod

=encoding UTF-8

=head1 NAME

dir-has-dot-subdirs - Test that a directory has dot subdirectories

=head1 VERSION

This document describes version 0.002 of dir-has-dot-subdirs (from Perl distribution App-FileTestUtils), released on 2019-09-29.

=head1 SYNOPSIS

On the command-line:

 % dir-has-dot-subdirs "foo" && echo "foo/ has dot subdirs"

=head1 DESCRIPTION

This is a simple CLI for L<File::MoreUtil>'s
L<dir_has_dot_subdirs|File::MoreUtil/dir_has_dot_subdirs>. It will exit 0 if
argument is a directory and has dot (a.k.a. hidden) subdirectories.

=head1 HOMEPAGE

Please visit the project's homepage at L<https://metacpan.org/release/App-FileTestUtils>.

=head1 SOURCE

Source repository is at L<https://github.com/perlancar/perl-App-FileTestUtils>.

=head1 BUGS

Please report any bugs or feature requests on the bugtracker website L<https://rt.cpan.org/Public/Dist/Display.html?Name=App-FileTestUtils>

When submitting a bug or request, please include a test-file or a
patch to an existing test-file that illustrates the bug or desired
feature.

